    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-29T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="432"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d432">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 659a.119/14</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-29T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8006. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 585. Referring further your 626, Embassy 10185, May 22, 5 p.m. We await
                    authorizing your adherence to agreement pending receipt of full text thereof. We
                    do not understand the proposals as to oil contracts, in view of discussions with
                    the British which are proceeding here regarding allotments to companies in
                    accordance with pre-war business.<note n="1" xml:id="d432fn1">See <ref
                            target="frus1918Supp01v01#pg_617">vol. 1, pp. 617</ref>
                        <hi rend="italic">et seq.</hi>
                    </note> Please cable more fully in regard to apparent exclusion of Standard Oil
                    Company which we understand has heretofore done practically all of the business
                    in Iceland.</p>
                <p>With reference to wool, we will take all wool obtainable provided this can be
                    secured at current United States option prices. Bigelow is familiar with this.
                    We will also take any amount of sheep skins at prices not exceeding the maximum
                    here which is 14 cents per foot New York, c.i.f.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
